#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing And Configuring Postfix"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing Mail First"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:55
msgid ""
"Before we configure postfix, we need to find out how mail will look when it "
"leaves the server, because we will probably want to change this. To do this, "
"start postfix:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:57
msgid "`systemctl start postfix`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:59
msgid "Then test it using mail command that is installed with mailx:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:61
msgid "`mail -s \"Testing from server\" myname@mydomain.com`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:63
msgid ""
"This will bring up a blank line. Simply type your testing message in here:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:65
msgid "`testing from the server`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:67
msgid "Now hit enter, and enter a single period:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:69
msgid "`.`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:71
msgid "The system will respond with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:73
msgid "`EOT`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:75
msgid ""
"Our purpose for doing this is to check to see how our mail looks to the "
"outside world, which we can get a feel for from the maillog that goes active "
"with the starting of postfix."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:77
msgid "Use this command to see the output of the log file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:79
msgid "`tail /var/log/maillog`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:81
msgid ""
"You should see something like this, although the log file may have different "
"domains for the email address, etc:"
msgstr ""

