#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:97
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring Postfix"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:100
msgid ""
"Since we aren't setting up a complete, fully functional mail server, the "
"configuration options that we will be using are not as extensive. The first "
"thing we need to do is to modify the _main.cf_ file (literally the main "
"configuration file for postfix), so let's make a backup first:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:102
msgid "`cp /etc/postfix/main.cf /etc/postfix/main.cf.bak`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:104
msgid "Then edit it:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:106
msgid "`vi /etc/postfix/main.cf`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:108
msgid ""
"In our example, our server name is going to be \"bruno\" and our domain name "
"is going to be \"ourdomain.com\". Find the line in the file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:110
msgid "`#myhostname = host.domain.tld`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:112
msgid ""
"You can either remove the remark (#) or you can add a new line under this "
"line. Based on our example, the line would read:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:114
msgid "`myhostname = bruno.ourdomain.com`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:116
msgid "Next, find the line for the domain name:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:118
msgid "`#mydomain = domain.tld`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:120
msgid "Either remove the remark and change it, or add a new line:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:122
msgid "`mydomain = ourdomain.com`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:124
msgid "Finally, go to the bottom of the file and add this line:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:126
msgid "`smtp_generic_maps = hash:/etc/postfix/generic`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:128
msgid ""
"Save your changes (in vi, that will be `Shift : wq!`) and exit the file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:130
msgid ""
"Before we continue editing the generic file, we need to see how email will "
"look. Specifically, we want to create the \"generic\" file that we "
"referenced in the _main.cf_ file above:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:132
msgid "`vi /etc/postfix/generic`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/email/postfix_reporting.md:134
msgid ""
"This file tells postfix how any email coming from this server should look. "
"Remember our test email and the log file? This is where we fix all of that:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
